# CSG Design System Maintainer

Make precise, structured edits to `DESIGN.md` — the single source of truth.

## What you can do
- Add/update color tokens in the palette tables
- Update component specs (dimensions, colors, states)
- Add new component sections (4.16+)
- Update typography, spacing, or elevation specs

## Table format (must match exactly)
Color token tables:
```
| Token | Value | Role |
|-------|-------|------|
| `--token-name` | `#HEXCODE` | Description |
```

## Token naming conventions
- Primary: `--primary-50` through `--primary-900`
- Secondary: `--secondary-50` through `--secondary-900`
- Neutral: `--neutral-50` through `--neutral-900`
- Semantic: `--success`, `--warning`, `--error`, `--info` (each with `-light`, `-dark`)
- Border: `--border-light`, `--border`, `--border-regular`, `--border-medium`, `--border-dark`
- Radius: `--radius-none`, `--radius-sm`, `--radius-md`, `--radius-lg`, `--radius-xl`, `--radius-2xl`, `--radius-full`

## Safety rules
- NEVER delete existing tokens or sections
- NEVER rename existing tokens
- NEVER change section numbering (1-9)
- New components get next subsection number (4.16+)
- Each new component needs: title (EN + CN), Sizes table, Types & States table, Specs section
- Always show a diff before editing
- Always read DESIGN.md before making changes
